                    </div>
                    <span>Essential XML commits the worst sin of any technical work: it assumes its readers are already familiar with the subject matter. Reading this book is is like joining a competitive high-level college course in mid-semester--one feels behind from the start.<p>Perhaps the authors feel that readers who would admit to a need for a more gradual approach to the material are beneath their consideration as being weak technically. It's unfortunate that omniscience is one of the assumed attributes of the hacker.<p>I for one am not omniscient, but prefer texts where the authors and editors have made a reasonable effort to present the material in a way accessible to readers with varying levels of prior expertise.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Concepts, concepts</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
